## Description
This script allow to use putty's sessions inside Windows Terminal.

### How to setup
1. `git clone git@github.com:SailorMax/psh.git`
2. right mouse click on ps1-file / Properties / `Unblock`
3. try to exec `psh.bat`. It has to output all putty session names and suggest to choose anyone to connect
4. add to `PATH` your clone-directory (SystemPropertiesAdvanced/Enviroment Variables.../User variables)
5. open Windows Terminal / "Command Prompt" / `psh` (as second argument you can use word to filter sessions list)

---
### Switch to Windows ssh-agent:
1. remove from memory git's `ssh-agent` (task manager), remove user's variables `SSH_AGENT_PID` and `SSH_AUTH_SOCK` (SystemPropertiesAdvanced/Enviroment Variables...), remove from `PATH` directory of Git's ssh (if it exists)
2. install via Windows "Optional features" `OpenSSH client`
3. prepare Git to use system's ssh: `git config --global core.sshCommand "'C:\Windows\System32\OpenSSH\ssh.exe'"`
4. setup bat-file to startup with system to add required keys to agent:
```bat
rem add default user's key (at ~/.ssh/)
ssh-add
rem add specific user's key
ssh-add path_to_key
```
